# Testing and Verification Rule

## Required sequence
1. Write or update focused tests first when behavior changes.
2. Implement until tests pass.
3. Refactor while keeping tests green.
4. Run the full verification commands before handoff or completion.

## Constraints
- Do not ship behavior changes without test coverage unless there is a clear, explicit reason.
- Prefer unit tests for business logic and targeted integration coverage for boundary behavior.
- Treat missing or failing tests as part of the work, not follow-up work.

## Required verification commands
```bash
npm run lint:fix
npm test
npm run build
GROK_API_KEY=dummy node dist/index.js validate examples/sample-playlist.json
GROK_API_KEY=dummy node dist/index.js config validate
```

Fix failures and rerun until clean.
